docs.lead_paragraph: LEAD: LAST year I turned 50, and it didn't bother me a bit. I was in great shape. I weighed 20 pounds less than when I got married 23 years before. I had no gray hair, and from the front only a dignified receding at the temples was visible, suggesting, if anything, accumulating wisdom. It was fun assuring friends that indeed I was 50, and hearing ''You sure don't look it,'' and ''I never would have guessed.

docs.lead_paragraph: LEAD: A SEVERE yet friendly rectangular box, the Schroder house is semidetached, at the end of a row of brick houses on Prins Hendriklaan in Utrecht. It looks startling today; when it was built in 1924, it must have shocked everyone.
